Square $ ABCD $ in the coordinate plane has vertices at the points $ A(1,1), B(-1,1), C(-1,-1), $ and $ D(1,-1). $ Consider the following five transformations:
- $ L $: a rotation of $ 90^\circ $ counterclockwise around the origin;
- $ R $: a rotation of $ 90^\circ $ clockwise around the origin;
- $ H $: a reflection across the $ x $-axis;
- $ V $: a reflection across the $ y $-axis;
- $ F $: a reflection across the line $ y=x $.
Each of these transformations maps the square onto itself, but changes the positions of the labeled vertices. How many sequences of 22 transformations chosen from $ \{L, R, H, V, F\} $ will send all of the labeled vertices back to their original positions?
A) $ 5^{20} $
B) $ 5^{21} $
C) $ 5^{22} $
D) $ 5^{23} $
